# Executive Summary
A local audio chat application was struggling with scaling costs, paying $3,000 â€“ $4,000 USD/month using a managed third-party WebRTC SDK. By migrating to a custom-built, cost-optimized AWS infrastructure, I reduced the monthly burn to $288 USD (a 90% saving) while achieving sub-30ms latency for the Middle Eastern market.


## The Problem: "The Managed Service Trap"
The client had ~200 concurrent users geographically concentrated in the Middle East. The legacy managed service charged aggressive per-minute fees, making growth financially unsustainable. There was no "economy of scale"; more users simply meant a bigger bill.

## The Solution: Architectural FinOps
1. High-Performance Networking
I designed a Multi-AZ VPC with 4 subnets (2 Public, 2 Private) to ensure high availability.
 * AWS Global Accelerator: Implemented to onboard traffic at the closest edge location. This reduced jitter and brought latency down to <30msâ€”a massive performance leap over the public internet.
 * Custom NAT Instances: Instead of the managed AWS NAT Gateway , I deployed self-managed NAT instances. This saved roughly $60/month in fixed fees and eliminated data processing "taxes."
2. Serverless Signaling Layer
I replaced the expensive third-party signaling SDK with Google Firestore.
 * Spark Tier Optimization: I architected the signaling state to remain within the No-Cost Spark Tier (50k reads/20k writes per day).
 * Result: Database baseline cost dropped to $0.00/month. The system is ready to scale to the "Pay-As-You-Go" tier only when traffic justifies the cost.
3. Compute Strategy: "Base and Burst"
To maximize the budget, I used a hybrid compute model:
 * Baseline (Savings Plan): 6 EC2 instances (4 for audio processing, 2 for NAT) were moved to a 1-Year AWS Savings Plan. This provided the reliability of On-Demand at a massive discount.
 * Burst (Spot Instances): The Auto Scaling Group (ASG) is configured to use Spot Instances for horizontal scaling. By leveraging spare AWS capacity, we scale up at 90% off regular prices.
 * Self-Healing: Linked the ASG to CloudWatch alarms to automatically replace failing nodes or scale during unexpected traffic spikes.
